			<h2>
			Sharing &amp; Privacy
			</h2>
			<p class="question">
			What is the “Public URL” and how does it work?
			</p>
			<p class="answer">
			The “Public URL” is a way for you to market yourself to schools and individuals who are not on the Tioki site yet. Maybe it's parent conferences and you want to showcase your professional background to start the year. Or Perhaps you are applying to a job that is not yet posting positions on Tioki. No worries! Simply click on “Edit Profile,” copy the unique “Public URL” link that we have assigned to you, and share it at your discretion.
			</p>
			<p class="question">
			Is my profile visible to everyone?
			</p>
			<p class="answer">
			You have control over the content the publicly displays on your profile. You can control your privacy settings <a href="#">here.</a>
			</p> 	
